Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Israeli Couscous{2.5%ounce}, @water{3/4%cup}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

While couscous cooks, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with half the @Turkish Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan; let cool for ~{1%minute}.

While chicken cooks, halve, peel, and finely dice @Yellow Onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Drain and rinse @Cannellini Beans{1}(drained and rinsed).

Melt @Butter{2%tablespoon} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add onion, half the @Shawarma Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper; cook, stirring constantly, until browned and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Reduce heat under pan to medium low; stir in beans, cooked couscous, and @Peas{4%ounce}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide couscous mixture between shallow bowls; top with chicken. Serve.

> Swap in chicken for pork.

> Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.